rComments: I took Econ 102 with fred my first semster and received an A.  You have to memorize the main concept of each chapter in his book, do decent on the homework, although it all comes down to the FINAL COUNTS FOR 45%.  The midterm and final are ESSAY form, so you need to know the stuff pretty solidly...definately look up his past exams online he repeats

Gotheil is a nut job. He rambles on about irrelevant material during lecture. The midterm worth 27% of our grade was not that bad I didn't study, but the Final which I actually took the time to study for I got a D! So even if you have an A like me going into the final you still will pull of a C! I recommend Gotheil to anyone looking for torture
Don't take his class, I got my only C in this university from his class.I am a junior now.
His lectures are pointless and boring. He teaches nothing, everything that i learned was from the book. In exams he wants you to not only answer the question but give some more BS that is irrelevant.
really really easy class! lectures are just a pleasure to be present for.  Recommend to anybody looking for an easy D.

Oh god, this class makes me want to pull out my fingernails. This professor just stands in front of class and tangents about life stories rarely touching on the topic that the lecture should apply to. Useless. And to top it all off, he mandates your attendance to this waste of an hour with pop quizzes. I'm just taking the dock to my grade.
I hope he discuss more material. He is funny and inspired, but not at all inspiring. And I'm afraid I'm not gonna get anything better than C+ for this boring class

Gottheil is infamous on campus. Well, his lectures usually consist of a 35-minute long illustration of an elementary transaction. Talk about tangents. He leaves the actual teaching for the TAs. However, the class definitely isn't hard. I suspect that many people expect an sleeper course, and then are surprised when they earn Cs or worse.
Boring class. Boring stories that he tells us. Just boring. Hard to get good grades on exams.

Not a bad guy. Tells stories like all old men do, but won't teach you much of anything on his own. All of the information is in the book and easy to absorb, but grading is total crap. It blows me away how a bunch of TA's who don't even speak english think they can grade essay tests. I have to find someone else for 103...

This professor is NOT a good choice. He is never on topic and the TA's don't know how to grade the exams! All essay question exams, and the final is worth half your grade. Take this course with a different professor!! Don't ruin your GPA by taking Gottheil's class.
Lectures weren't that helpful, but doesn't hurt to go. Do your hwk and pop quizzes, read the book THOROUGHLY.. and it'll be an easy A. That's how I got mine.

He is a fine professor, but you MUST read the book thoroughly. The reason people rate him so low is because they think they can get by just be attending class (or even less). Read the book, and take notes of anything that is a list (e.g. factors that affect the supply curve) or a definition/equation (e.g. MRP). Memorize them and you will be fine.

Don't listen to the other comments. He knows what he is talking about, is helpful if you go to him, and his lectures are clear and entertaining. If you have an interest in econ, you'll love the course. READ the textbook, it's extremely important.

This class was an easy A.  Lecture is pointless.  Get with other students and exchange study materials that the TAs provide.  Use that and read the book (READ TO UNDERSTAND) and you shouldn't have a problem.  This class will be hard if you have a reading comprehension problem and don't think studying is a fact of life in college.

Honestly if you are a starting freshman and you can avoid this class then i would surely do so because his grading policies are so outrageous that it isn't worth jeopordizing your GPA. It's true that reading the book really helps and that his letures are pointless, but amount of effort is not necessarily reflected in your grades. The man is quirky.

Tough class, boring lecture ( exactly what is written in the text book). However, you must go to class b/c of random pop quizzes I studied a lot for both the midterm and final with an high b's on both, but aplia and pop quizzes help raise your grade if you do them.

I thought Gottheil was pretty entertaining, but lectures could be boring. The class can be pretty difficult. If you don't read the book, do the homework, or know his examples and graphs, then you will probably fail. The book is what you really learn from, so make sure you read it and understand it.

This class was easy but the T.A. dont speak english so know their language because I rose my midterm grade by 30% because the T.A. goes by the key and if you put rise rather than increase on a paper that means you lose 5 points. He is very non-involved and doesnt even grade. He also goes on tangents and never gets back on topic.

Snicker Bars and Jelly Beans.  That's all I remember from lecture.  Boring Class, material is not hard, but the tests are long and he makes the questions hard.  The TAs grade the tests really hard and that is what will bring your grade down.  I recommend taking this class at a junior college
